title: NATO chief warns Europe can’t defend itself without US as tensions rise over Greenland
description: NATO Secretary-General Mark Rutte warned European leaders they cannot defend themselves without U.S. support, saying Europe would need 10% GDP spending on defense.

title: Bessent warns Canada breaking from the US on trade would be a ‘disaster’

description: In Davos at the World Economic Forum last week, Carney condemned economic coercion by great powers on smaller countries without mentioning Trump’s name.

title: Neil Young's gift to Greenland: Free access to his entire music catalog
description: Neil Young is offering free access to his entire music catalog to residents of Greenland. He announced this on his blog on Tuesday in a bid to ease stress amid tensions involving the U.S. and NATO.

description: President Donald Trump is taking a more conciliatory approach with Democratic leaders in Minnesota. This change follows the second fatal shooting there by federal agents this month.

description: India and the European Union have reached a free trade agreement to deepen economic and strategic ties.

title: Consumer confidence collapses to lowest level since 2014 | CNN Business
description: America’s economic mood deteriorated in January to its lowest level in more than a decade as consumers fretted about geopolitical tensions, affordability and President Donald Trump’s unrelenting trade war.

title: ‘We cannot rely on the United States, period,’ says fmr. leader of Canadian opposition | CNN
description: Bianna Golodryga speaks with Michael Ignatieff, the former Canadian opposition leader, about the growing tensions between U.S. President Donald Trump and Canadian Prime Minister Mark Carney.

title: Analysis: Twice within a week, Trump is forced to tone down big second-term power grabs | CNN Politics
description: The president sent his border czar Tom Homan to the state in an implicit sign of lost confidence in two bombastic subordinates, Homeland Security Secretary Kristi Noem and top Border Patrol official Greg Bovino.

title: India and Europe, both stung by Trump, turn to each other in a ‘mother of all deals’ on trade | CNN
description: The European Union and India agreed a free trade deal Tuesday, the largest such deal ever clinched by either side, as they contend with an erratic trade policy from key trading partner the United States.

title: For Britain, China remains a ‘threat’ – but one worth doing business with | CNN
description: Prime Minister Keir Starmer is the first British leader to travel to China in eight years, on a trip dominated by questions over global trade and security concerns.

title: Video: F.A.A. Ignored Safety Concerns Prior to Collision Over Potomac, N.T.S.B. Says
description: The National Transportation Safety Board said that a “multitude of errors” led to the collision between a military helicopter and a commercial jet, killing 67 people last January.

title: India, EU reach landmark trade deal to slash tariffs on most goods
description: India and the EU struck a long‑delayed deal that will slash tariffs on most goods, aiming to boost two‑way trade and reduce reliance on the United States amid growing global trade tensions.

title: World Cup boycott? With people ‘dying on the street’, a German soccer exec wants a discussion
description: “It is clearly time to at least discuss a boycott,” Goettlich, who is also president of Bundesliga club St. Pauli, tells The Athletic.

title: Ex-FIFA president Sepp Blatter joins those calling for boycott of World Cup in U.S.
description: Former FIFA president Sepp Blatter is backing a proposed fan boycott of World Cup matches in the United States because of the conduct of President Trump and his administration at home and abroad.

title: Italian officials voice outrage at the presence of U.S. ICE agents at the 2026 Olympics
description: U.S. Homeland Security agents provided security support at past Olympics. But after violence by ICE agents in Minneapolis, some Italian officials say an ICE unit is unwelcome in Milan Cortina.

title: After rocky start, Bari Weiss plans cuts, adds commentators at CBS News
description: CBS News Editor-in-Chief Bari Weiss came in with a mandate to reshape coverage. She laid out her strategy in a staff meeting Tuesday.

title: Can Europe sell America? : The Indicator from Planet Money
description: “Sell America.” There’s new talk of how Europe could turn the economic screws on the U.S. after President Trump’s play for Greenland. Selling U.S. Treasury bonds is one way. description: NATO Secretary-General Mark Rutte insisted Monday that Europe is incapable of defending itself without U.S. military support and would have to more than double current military spending targets to be able to do so.

description: Neil Young offered Greenland free access to his music due to the "unwarranted stress and threats you are experiencing" from President Donald Trump.
